.START 

AD REVENUE: Times Mirror Co. 's ad revenue at its Newspaper Publishing Group rose 1.8% for the four weeks ended Sept. 3 to $120.8 million from $118.7 million a year earlier.
For the first 35 weeks of the year, total ad revenue rose 5.6% to $1.12 billion from $1.06 billion a year earlier.
This year's cumulative results included five more days, including a Sunday. 

JOINT VENTURE: DTH Media Inc. 's Dallas Times Herald signed a joint-venture agreement to print and distribute Investor's Daily in the North Texas area, effective Nov. 7.
Investor's Daily is owned by William O'Neil & Co., Los Angeles. 

WHO'S NEWS: MCA Inc. named Tom Martin vice president of print advertising for its Universal Pictures unit.
He had been director of print advertising. 

